monitoring.title: Patients who have had BP measured
monitoring.header: Patients with opportunities for BP measurement

items.name: No opportunities
items.desc: Patients who have had no contact with the practice
items.main: These are patients that you have had no contact with.

items.name: Face-to-face
items.desc: Patients who have seen a clinician in GP practice
items.main: These are patients you have had direct contact with (e.g. face-to-face or telephone).

items.name: Non face-to-face
items.desc: Patients who have not seen a clinician in the practice but had some sort of contact e.g. telephone calls, picking up repeat prescriptions, letters
items.main: These are patients you have had indirect contact with (e.g. prescriptions or letters).

items.name: Suboptimal medication
items.desc: Patients who could have their medication optimised
items.main: These are patients who have had a high blood pressure reading taken in the last 2 months.

items.name: Medication non-adherence
items.desc: Patients who may not be picking up their repeat medication regularly
items.main: These are patients who have had a high blood pressure reading and their medication has been changed over 2 months ago, but they have not yet had their blood pressure measured again.

items.name: Referral to secondary care
items.desc: Patients who are on maximal anti-hypertensive medication
items.main: These are patients who have had a high blood pressure reading taken and could have their medication optimised.

items.name: One-off high BP reading
items.desc: Patients who had a high blood pressure reading in the last 2 months that previously had controlled blood pressure

items.name: Recently optimised medication
items.desc: Patients who had a high blood pressure reading and then had their medication increased

items.name: White coat hypertension
items.desc: Patients who may have high blood pressure because they are anxious when they come to the practice

items.name: Palliative Care
items.desc: Patients who are receiving palliative care
